== Features In Testing ==
(Added in current implementation session - not yet runtime tested)

1. Text Blocks (2D & 3D)
   - New object types: text, text3d
   - Properties: content, font family, font size, color, background, alignment, bold, italic
   - Canvas-based text rendering applied as texture
   - Full serialization/deserialization support

2. Screen/Media Objects
   - New object type: screen
   - Supports solid color or uploaded image display
   - FileReader-based image upload in properties panel
   - Full serialization/deserialization support

3. Camera Objects
   - New object type: camera
   - Properties: FOV, near clip, far clip
   - Appears in Object Library under "Media" category
   - Full serialization/deserialization support

4. Cross-World Teleport
   - Teleport config expanded with crossWorld toggle and targetWorld selector
   - checkTeleportBlocks() rewritten to search stored world data
   - Switches worlds and repositions player with relative offset

5. Teleport Invisible by Default During Play
   - 'teleport' added to hiddenInGame list in createMesh()
   - Teleports are hidden when entering playtest mode

6. Ground/Grid Textures
   - 5 procedural textures: grass, dirt, stone, sand, snow
   - Dropdown selector in Grid Settings panel
   - Procedural canvas generation (256x256 with noise patches)
   - Full serialization/deserialization of texture selection

7. New Block Texture Patterns
   - Wood (wavy grain pattern)
   - Cobblestone (irregular rounded shapes with mortar)
   - Marble (veined pattern)
   - Added to texture paint pattern dropdown

8. Image Upload as Custom Texture
   - Upload button in Texture Paint panel
   - FileReader loads image, applies as THREE.Texture
   - Works with paint mode click-to-apply system
   - Custom image cleared when selecting a built-in pattern

9. Terrain Walkability Fix
   - Terrain objects now default to geometry-based collision mode
   - Players can walk on sculpted terrain surfaces properly
